1
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:36,720
Did you bring it?

2
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:41,240
The computer is ready, Officer Shao.

3
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:42,040
What Officer Shao?

4
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:43,560
I haven't been a cop for a long time.

5
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:44,420
Here's a phone.

6
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:45,600
Can you check

7
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:47,560
the location of the person who called it?

8
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:48,690
How did you get this?

9
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:50,920
This is a one-on-one phone.

10
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:52,050
It's encrypted.

11
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:54,000
And it usually uses satellite signals.

12
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:54,920
Stop talking nonsense.

13
00:00:54,920 --> 00:00:56,450
Just tell me if you can do it.

14
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,160
I don't like to hear that.

15
00:00:58,520 --> 00:00:59,440
You were dismissed.

16
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:00,440
I wasn't.

17
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:03,880
I still have to go to the police station to help out every few days.

18
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:05,010
I wouldn't be rusty.

19
00:01:05,160 --> 00:01:07,560
But this is the first time I've worked here.

20
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:08,760
What's your deal?

21
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:09,720
And?

22
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,130
What's going on?

23
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:12,800
Nothing.

24
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,440
Why are you talking so much nonsense now?

25
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:15,680
Tell me how long it will take.

26
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:16,760
About 40 minutes.

27
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:21,240
No, I have to take this phone right now.

28
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:22,500
Is there any other way?

29
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:24,039
What else can be done?

30
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:26,860
Give me your phone.

31
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:31,289
I'll install a program on both phones.

32
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:34,360
Then anyone who calls this special phone

33
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,000
will be automatically forwarded to your phone.

34
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,800
Leave the special phone with me.

35
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:38,840
When I'm done,

36
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:39,640
I'll call you.

37
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:09,080
Look at your 3 o'clock.

38
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:11,320
I told you to bring the money.

39
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:12,400
Why didn't you?

40
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,440
There's a bunch of punks.

41
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,240
What's wrong?

42
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,480
Get a video from Blondie.

43
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:18,480
What video?

44
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:20,000
He knows what video.

45
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:22,200
Call me after you get it.

46
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:27,079
How many times have I said it?

47
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:28,320
Give me the money.

48
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:29,079
Understood?

49
00:02:29,079 --> 00:02:30,140
Do you understand?

50
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:35,960
Met some girls last night.

51
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:38,160
Let's introduce them to the guys later.

52
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,640
What's for dinner?

53
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:40,480
What else?

54
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:42,360
Just grab something at Xiyuan Food Street.

55
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,920
Do you want to die?

56
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:45,560
Pisses me off.

57
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:50,280
Same time, same place tomorrow.

58
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,940
If you don't give me the money,

59
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:57,920
Who are you?

60
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,500
It doesn't matter who I am.

61
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,360
And I'm not interested in your business.

62
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,360
Then what's the meaning of this?

63
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,080
Trying to play hero?

64
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,600
Let me tell you.

65
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,600
Give me the video.

66
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:13,960
What video?

67
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,200
You know what I'm talking about.

68
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,000
Give me the video,

69
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,120
and I'll leave right away.

70
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,579
Looking for trouble, huh?

71
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,160
Fine.

72
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:22,960
Guys, teach him a lesson.

73
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,240
Come on.

74
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,600
Hurry up.

75
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:28,680
Come on.

76
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:01,380
How's it going?

77
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:01,960
Done.

78
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:04,440
Found the location of the person who called you last time.

79
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,040
I'll send it to you now.

80
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:06,530
Okay.

81
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,040
Hello.

82
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:21,250
Didn't you like the last phone?

83
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,120
If you try to break the rules again,

84
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:27,980
the gift you receive will be much heavier than this.

85
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,890
Heavier in the physical sense.

86
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:32,159
Okay, I know I was wrong.

87
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,000
Don't hurt my daughter.

88
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:38,000
If you didn't like that phone, forget it.

89
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,520
I'll give you this new one.

90
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:42,560
Also, the mission isn't going very smoothly, is it?

91
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,640
You need to step up.

92
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,360
The doctor will be here shortly.

93
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,020
Please wait here for a moment.

94
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:58,960
Mrs. Liu,

95
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,640
could you help me clear the takeout on the table too?

96
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:02,560
Dr. Wen,

97
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,040
you had takeout for lunch again?

98
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,200
Yeah.

99
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,760
I don't like cooking.

100
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,960
That won't do.

101
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:12,360
Look at them, they all cook and bring their own meals.

102
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,730
It's hygienic and healthy.

103
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:17,040
Besides,

104
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,640
as a young girl,

105
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,280
if you can't cook,

106
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,640
how will you find a boyfriend?

107
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:28,280
All done.

108
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,050
Don't wash your hair when you get back.

109
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:34,360
You're hurt too.

110
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:41,159
Didn't the doctor tell you no strenuous exercise after surgery?

111
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:43,840
You're bleeding so much. It needs to be treated right away.

112
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,640
I'm fine.

113
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:46,280
Let me treat it for you.

114
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,400
I said no need.

115
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:48,610
Let's go.

116
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:01,640
No need.

117
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,040
Just feel it with your hand.

118
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,080
Let me see. Is it hot?

119
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,040
Is it? Is it?

120
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:05,800
You really have a fever.

121
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:06,520
Let go of my hand first.

122
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:06,920
Don't.

123
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:07,960
Let go of my hand first.

124
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,000
Do you have it or not?

125
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,330
Are you running a fever?

126
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,280
This is my sister.

127
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:13,240
If you harass her again,

128
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,570
I'll chop your hand off.

129
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,320
Thank you.

130
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,340
Why are you back again?

131
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:23,600
You do CT scans here, right?

132
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,160
Right up ahead.

133
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,520
How long will the results take?

134
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,120
Very soon.

135
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:48,380
What's the countdown on your wristband?

136
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:55,880
Thank you.

137
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:00,720
There's a shadow in your abdomen.

138
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:04,120
But its shape is too regular.

139
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,480
What is this?

140
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:09,920
What kind of surgery did you have before?

141
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:12,570
Is it an artificial organ implant?

142
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:13,800
No.

143
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:16,090
Your current condition is uncertain.

144
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,370
You can't leave yet.

145
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:18,800
We need to run more tests.

146
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,240
Your life is in danger right now.

147
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,720
I have things to do.

148
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:33,720
Do you know that blond guy who bullied you today?

149
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:34,520
No.

150
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,320
He bullied me a few times before.

151
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:38,120
I just know he hangs around here.

152
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,840
Do you know where to find him?

153
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:40,570
I don't know.

154
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:46,560
I heard he lives in Beicheng International.

155
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:48,760
Remember this.

156
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:49,720
If this happens again,

157
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:52,840
fight back when there are few people.

158
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:54,960
If you are always so weak,

159
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,840
they will bully you even more.

160
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:59,840
When there are many people, don't just stand there.

161
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:00,400
Run.

162
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:01,280
Got it?

163
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:04,220
Call the police if you have to.

164
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:05,520
All right.

165
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:06,520
Go home.

166
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:13,560
Hello.

167
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:15,280
Is there a young man in our neighborhood,

168
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:15,920
short,

169
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:16,440
quite thin,

170
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,680
and has dyed blond hair?

171
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,360
Does that ring a bell?

172
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,220
No impression.

173
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:19,800
Hello.

174
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:20,680
Hello.

175
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:23,400
Have you seen a guy with blond hair around here?

176
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:23,920
Not very tall.

177
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:24,680
A boy.

178
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:25,960
I don't remember him.

179
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:29,800
With blonde hair.

180
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,200
A short and skinny boy.

181
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,060
Never seen him.

182
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,480
With blonde hair,

183
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,600
and quite skinny. You haven't seen him?

184
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,460
Never seen him.

185
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,000
Thank you.

186
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,480
What are we eating tonight?

187
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,320
What else?

188
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:57,050
Let's just grab something at Xiyuan Food Street.

189
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:43,640
Guys,

190
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:44,880
let's teach him a lesson.
